The Telegraph - Calcutta
 SA to help Zimbabwe
Durban: The United Cricket Board of South Africa (UCBSA) on Thursday said it will assist Zimbabwe in resolving its impasse in the larger interest of the game. UCB CEO Gerald Majola said board president Ray Mali had been given a full mandate to help Zimbabwe in solving the crisis. I spoke to the president (Mali) on Thursday and he confirmed that the general council of the UCB has given him a mandate to offer assistance in seeking a solution to the current problems facing Zimbabwe cricket. He said Mali would be attending an ICC executive board meeting in Dubai on June 10 to discuss the Zimbabwe situation.  (PTI)  Copyright 
